{
  "texts": [
    "Prompt 3, which was intended to identify cases where participants described a conspiracy theory but also expressed skepticism, was applied only to the raw responses.",
    "To evaluate the reliability of the ratings provided across different prompts, we used Gwet's AC1 coefficient.",
    "The percent agreement across raters was.86, reflecting an AC1 =.77 (95% CI [.76,.79]), with 60.2% of statements classified as a conspiracy theory under all four prompts (69.3% in Sample 1 and 55.3% in Sample 2; see Tables S5-S6).",
    "To adjudicate between the prompts, the first author coded a random subset of 200 theories, which revealed a stronger agreement with Prompt 1 (AC1 =.80 [.72,.89]) than Prompt 2 (AC1 =.71 [.62,.82]) or Prompt 3 (AC1 =.56 [.44,.67]).",
    "Hence, we proceeded with Prompt 1 in our primary analyses."
  ]
}